void PathBasedAlgo::initialise ( )

Initialises solution structure of the algorithm. Usually it performs AON assignment.

Implements EqAlgo.

bool PathBasedAlgo::mainLoop ( ODSet *  odSet)
protectedvirtual

Performs main operation made during one iteration for a given O-D pair. It implements equilibration I. Equilibration II over-rides this method. For details see PathBasedAlgoEQII.

Returns
true if current O-D pair was equilibrated, false otherwise. The return value is needed only for equilibration II.

Reimplemented in PathBasedAlgoEqII.
